#compdef mysql_random_data_load
# =============================================================================
# mysql_random_data_load — Percona-Lab's "MySQL random data
#                            loader" — a Go CLI that introspects
#                            an existing MySQL table schema and
#                            populates it with N rows of plausible
#                            RANDOM TEST DATA matching the column
#                            types + constraints.  Distinct from
#                            generic data generators by being
#                            SCHEMA-AWARE:
#                              - Reads the target table's column
#                                definitions via INFORMATION_SCHEMA
#                              - Generates random data appropriate
#                                to each column's TYPE (INT range,
#                                VARCHAR length, ENUM values, DATE
#                                range, DECIMAL precision)
#                              - Respects FOREIGN KEY CONSTRAINTS
#                                by sampling values from referenced
#                                tables (with --fk-samples-factor
#                                + --max-fk-samples controlling
#                                sampling intensity)
#                              - PARALLEL multi-threaded insertion
#                                via --max-threads
#                              - CONFIGURABLE bulk insert size
#                                (--bulk-size) for throughput
#                                tuning
#                              - PRINT mode (--print) emits SQL
#                                without executing — useful for
#                                CI/CD pipeline integration
#                            Used by Percona's database engineers
#                            for benchmark/load-test setup, by
#                            QA teams generating realistic test
#                            data, and by database academic
#                            researchers studying query patterns
#                            against synthetic but realistic
#                            datasets.
#
# Author:  Percona Laboratories (Percona LLC — the leading
#          open-source MySQL/PostgreSQL/MongoDB consultancy +
#          tooling vendor) — actively maintained as part of
#          Percona's MySQL operational toolkit alongside
#          pt-toolkit, pmm, etc.
# Source:  https://github.com/Percona-Lab/mysql_random_data_load
#          https://github.com/Percona-Lab/mysql_random_data_load/blob/master/main.go
# CLI:     main.go — uses `gopkg.in/alecthomas/kingpin.v2`
#          (already documented in R567 _devd as the 49th Go
#          CLI library variant — fluent-builder argv parser).
#          Headline observability library: `github.com/gosuri/
#          uiprogress` for real-time progress bar display
#          during multi-million-row data inserts.
# Library: gosuri/uiprogress (gosuri uiprogress)
#          ("A Go library for rendering progress bars in
#           terminal applications" — Greg Osuri — released
#           2015 as a TERMINAL PROGRESS-BAR LIBRARY for Go
#           with FLEXIBLE LAYOUT + CUSTOM DECORATORS.  Part
#           of Greg Osuri's `gosuri/ui*` family of terminal
#           UI libraries (uiprogress, uilive, uitable, cli-app)
#           that established many of the FOUNDATIONAL PATTERNS
#           for Go terminal libraries before the modern Charm
#           ecosystem emerged.  Distinguishing features:
#             - MULTI-BAR SUPPORT with automatic terminal-line
#               coordination (via gosuri/uilive — same author)
#             - PER-BAR DECORATORS for custom prefix/suffix
#               (percent / current/total / elapsed / ETA)
#             - WIDTH-AUTO-FIT to terminal columns
#             - ANSI escape sequences for cursor positioning
#               and line clearing
#             - PROGRESS aggregation across multiple bars)
# License: Apache-2.0 (mysql_random_data_load); MIT (uiprogress)
# Status:  mysql_random_data_load — 303+ stars on Percona-Lab/
#          mysql_random_data_load, actively maintained as part
#          of Percona's MySQL operational toolkit; uiprogress
#          — 2000+ stars on gosuri/uiprogress, 30M+ all-time
#          pkg.go.dev downloads, foundational dependency of
#          many 2015-2018 era Go CLI tools (mysql_random_data_
#          load, percona-toolkit-go, video-downloader, podium,
